.TH "hpt3x3_set_piomode" 9 "hpt3x3_set_piomode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hpt3x3_set_piomode \- PIO setup
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" hpt3x3_set_piomode
.BI "(struct ata_port *ap "  ","
.BI "struct ata_device *adev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ap" 12
ATA interface
.IP "adev" 12
device on the interface

Set our PIO requirements. This is fairly simple on the HPT3x3 as
all we have to do is clear the MWDMA and UDMA bits then load the
mode number.
